===Etymology===
{{borrowing|fr|en|lang=en}} ''[[#French|chamois]]'', from {{etyl|cel-gau|en}} {{term|camox|lang=cel-gau}} (5th c., Polemius Silvius), probably from an extinct Alpine language (Raetic, Ligurian). Compare also {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|gamiza|lang=goh}} {{gloss|"chamois"}} (whence modern German {{term|Gämse|lang=de}}).

